  "local_port": 38332,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is it like being a student at UBC?",
  "response": "Being a student at the University of British Columbia (UBC) offers a unique and enriching experience, combining academic rigor with a vibrant campus life. Here\u2019s a snapshot of what it\u2019s like:\n\n### Academics\n- **Diverse Programs:** UBC offers a wide range of undergraduate and graduate programs across various faculties, including Arts, Science, Engineering, Business, and more.\n- **Research Opportunities:** As a leading research university, UBC provides numerous opportunities for students to engage in cutting-edge research projects.\n- **Renowned Faculty:** Students learn from some of the world\u2019s leading experts in their fields.\n\n### Campus Life\n- **Beautiful Campus:** UBC\u2019s Vancouver campus is renowned for its stunning natural surroundings, located on the tip of a peninsula with views of mountains and the ocean.\n- **Student Organizations:** There are hundreds of clubs and organizations catering to a wide range of interests, from academic and professional groups to cultural and recreational clubs.\n- **Events and Activities:** The university hosts numerous events throughout the year, including concerts, lectures, sports events, and cultural celebrations.\n\n### Facilities\n- **Libraries and Study Spaces:** UBC boasts several libraries and numerous study spaces, both quiet and collaborative, to suit different needs.\n- **Recreation and Wellness:** The campus has extensive athletic facilities, including gyms, pools, and sports fields, as well as wellness programs and services.\n- **Housing:** On-campus housing options range from traditional dormitories to more apartment-style living, with a strong sense of community.\n\n### Location\n- **Vancouver:** Being in Vancouver means students have access to a dynamic city with a rich cultural scene, outdoor activities, and a diverse population. The city offers numerous opportunities for internships, jobs, and networking.\n- **Transportation:** UBC is well-connected by public transit, making it easy to explore the city and surrounding areas.\n\n### International Community\n- **Diversity:** UBC attracts students from all over the world, creating a multicultural and inclusive environment.\n- **Global Perspectives:** The university emphasizes global citizenship, offering various international programs and exchanges.\n\n### Support Services\n- **Academic Advising:** UBC provides robust academic support, including advising, tutoring, and writing centers.\n- **Career Services:** The university offers career counseling, workshops, and job fairs to help students prepare for their future careers.\n- **Health and Counseling:** Comprehensive health and mental health services are available to support students\u2019 well-being.\n\n### Challenges\n- **Competitive Environment:** Given UBC\u2019s reputation, the academic environment can be highly competitive.\n- **Cost of Living:** Vancouver is known for its high cost of living, which can be a challenge for students managing their finances.\n\nOverall, being a student at UBC is a rewarding experience that combines academic excellence with a rich and diverse campus life, set in one of the most beautiful cities in the world.\n```",
